freecli() core function.
DESCRIPTION_END

void freecli(cli_s *cli);


frees all ezcli-owned piece of memory which
are the 'cli_s' struct and options initialized using 'allocopt()'.

see 'ezdocs cli_s' for explanation of what 'cli_s' is.
see 'ezdocs allocopt' for explanation of what 'allocopt()' does.

freecli() is also run when ezcli comes across
a syntax error and has to exit.
